
[1]scurvy-grass

   SCUR'VY-GRASS, n. A plant of the genus Cochlearia; spoonwort. It grows
   on rocks near the sea, has an acrid, bitter taste, and is remarkable as
   a remedy for the scurvy. It is eaten raw as a salad.
